May 7, 1995<BR>
Fahassi, a reporter for French-language Algerian radio and formerly a contributor 
to <CITE>Al-Forqane, </CITE>
a weekly organ of the Islamic Salvation Front (FIS) that was banned in March 1992, 
was arrested by state security services. Officials have refused to acknowledge his 
arrest. His family believes he is in a secret detention center and fears for his 
life.<BR>
