<STRONG>WESTERN SAHARA (1)<BR>
</STRONG>
<BR>
<STRONG>Bahi Mohamed Ould Deif<BR>
</STRONG>
<CITE>Imprisoned: </CITE>
1986<BR>
Bahi Mohamed, a Moroccan journalist, disappeared in 1986 while reporting from Tindouf, 
in western Algeria. After his disappearance, an Algerian newspaper reported that 
he had been arrested by the Polisario Front--a group fighting for an independent state 
in Western Sahara--for plotting the assassination of its general secretary, Mohamed 
Abdelaziz. Abdelaziz's claim that Bahi Mohamed is at liberty and free to return to 
Morocco has not been confirmed. The Moroccan National Press Syndicate maintains he 
is still being held against his will.<BR>
