<BR>
<STRONG>Omar Ouartilan,</STRONG>
 <CITE>El Khabar<BR>
</CITE>
<CITE>Date of Death: </CITE>
October 3, 1995<BR>
<CITE>Place of Death: </CITE>
Belcourt, Algiers<BR>
Ouartilan, editor in chief of the independent Arabic-language daily <CITE>El Khabar, </CITE>
was shot to death at a newsstand near his home in the Belcourt district of Algiers 
on his way to work at the nearby Maison de la Presse Tahar Djaout. Despite the death 
threats against all journalists, Ouartilan refused protection and would not change 
the route he took between his home and office.<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>Saida Djebaili,</STRONG>
 <CITE>Al-Hayat al-Arabia</CITE>
<BR>
<CITE>Date of Death: </CITE>
