<P><table border=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0> <tr valign=top><td rowspan=3><img src="ccnlearn.gif" width=155 height=80 border=0></td></td><td colspan=2><a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/bbar"><IMG SRC="bbar.gif" width=215 height=20 BORDER=0 ISMAP></A></td></tr><tr valign=top><td rowspan=2><img src="nherism.gif" width=55 height=60 border=0></td><td><img src="blank.gif" width=160 height=35 border=0></td></tr><tr><td><img src="blank.gif" width=160 height=25 border=0></td></tr></table>
<P>
<P><meta name="description" content="NHERI is the National Home Education Research Institute.  The institute has offices in Salem, Oregon and in Washington, DC. Dr. Brian Ray founded the institute in 1990 as a 501(c)3 non-profit research organization, and is the president of the institute. He lives in Salem, Oregon and heads up the West Coast Home Office of NHERI. Dr. Ray is responsible for doing and collecting research about home schooling, publishing the research journal called the Home School Researcher, and coordinating the day-to-day activities of the institute. William (Bill) Lloyd is a researcher and branch manager of NHERI's Washington DC office. Mr. Lloyd is also a statistician at the US Bureau of the Census in Suitland, MD; his duties with NHERI include working with the media on articles concerning home schooling, speaking to national and state legislators about home schooling research, and assisting Dr. Ray with his research duties."> <BR>
